This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D shape synthesis and modeling. It may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with generating 3D shapes. Additionally, it involves the use of a loss function, which is a common technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a novel methodology for training 3D generative models, which could also fall under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
